parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to Brake Line Rupture
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake fluid leaking from the brake lines

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unwanted activation of the anti-lock brake system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to Master Cylinder or Vacuum Booster Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder or vacuum booster can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotor can cause the brake pedal to vibrate or pulsate, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or injuries.
The malfunction of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
The intermittent failure of the windshield wipers can cause poor visibility, especially during rainy or snowy conditions, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: causing poor visibility while driving. The wipers may need to be restarted by jerking the arm or stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch or shift lever can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle can be shifted out of park without the key in the ignition or without pressing the brake pedal
causing the vehicle to roll or move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip out of gear, or fail to shift properly, leading to accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The transmission slips in and out of overdrive
or makes loud noises while shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the four-wheel drive system can cause loss of traction, leading to accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The four-wheel drive system fails to engage
or the indicator light does not illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the universal joint can cause the driveshaft to drop out, leading to loss of power and control.
symptoms: Noise is heard prior to failure
and the universal joint drops out while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axle seal can cause loss of power and control.
The failure of the drive axle can cause loss of power and control.
symptoms: Something within the drive axle is loose and ready to fall off.
